trend_summary: Across the series, scattered forest gaps are replaced by housing tracts and enlarged light-industrial campuses, slowly tightening the street grid. Commercial roofs multiply near the center, while several small ponds/parks appear to offset tree loss. Overall built-up footprint grows moderately without high-rise concentration, keeping a leafy, automobile-oriented character.
notable_changes: Progressive infill of wooded lots by single-family subdivisions in north-central blocks.
Expansion of central light-industrial park with new large white-roof warehouses.
Construction of a sports/athletic complex in the southeastern corner, replacing open land.
New storm-water ponds and small recreational greenspaces scattered near built additions.
Minor extension of riverside greenway and bridge approach improvements along the southwest edge.
